article.description: — Ryan Allen scored a season-high 25 points as Delaware edged past UNC Wilmington 67-62 on Sunday.
article.headline: Allen scores 25 to carry Delaware over UNC Wilmington 67-62
article.linkText: Allen scores 25 to carry Delaware over UNC Wilmington 67-62
article.story: WILMINGTON, N.C. -- — Ryan Allen scored a season-high 25 points as Delaware edged past UNC Wilmington 67-62 on Sunday. Dylan Painter had 15 points, 15 rebounds and three blocks for Delaware (5-7, 3-4 Colonial Athletic Association), which broke its four-game road losing streak. Leading 37-36 at the half, Delaware held UNC Wilmington to a season-low 26 second-half points on 8 of 26 shooting (31%). Ty Gadsden had 14 points for the Seahawks (7-6, 1-3). Joe Pridgen added 12 points and eight rebounds. Jaylen Sims had 12 points and six rebounds. UNC Wilmington defeated Delaware 77-70 on Saturday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
